WEBVTT

00:08.927 --> 00:10.927
SUBTITLES BY
LUIS-SUBS

00:10.928 --> 00:12.350
It's interesting.
I didn't think about this.

00:12.429 --> 00:15.148
It's like living a lie.

00:15.224 --> 00:19.855
I didn't live a lot of lies,
but I lived one big one.

00:19.937 --> 00:23.407
You know, it's different, I guess.
Maybe it's not.

00:23.482 --> 00:25.234
But yeah, it's...

00:27.945 --> 00:29.822
And what I said in
there with just how

00:29.905 --> 00:32.033
this story is
all over the place,

00:32.115 --> 00:34.834
and there are these two

00:34.910 --> 00:40.633
just complete
opposite narratives.

00:42.292 --> 00:46.013
You know, the only person

00:46.088 --> 00:48.807
that can actually
start to let people

00:48.966 --> 00:51.685
understand what
the true narrative is is me.

00:52.636 --> 00:54.058
And you should know that
better than anybody.

00:54.137 --> 01:00.941
Let's get to the real nature and
the real detail of the story.

01:01.019 --> 01:05.570
'Cause we haven't
heard it yet, is the truth.

01:09.987 --> 01:11.284
Lance, how you feeling?

01:11.405 --> 01:12.748
Good. I'm very good.

01:15.659 --> 01:17.627
Nervous. But that's good.

01:19.162 --> 01:21.881
Always nervous for these.

01:22.791 --> 01:24.793
Not a lot of room for error.

01:25.836 --> 01:28.510
So makes it interesting.

01:28.589 --> 01:31.388
Oh, yeah.
Welcome to the party.

